cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper proposes a neural network for motion estimation in videos that incorporates geometry and depth information. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper deals with robotics (cs.RO) as it involves estimating camera motion and object motions. The paper also involves machine learning (cs.LG) as it proposes a neural network architecture. The paper also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with learning from data. Finally, the paper involves graphics (cs.GR) as it deals with generating optical flow and warping frames.
